<abstract><t>This document describes BagIt, a set of hierarchical file layout conventions for storage and transfer of arbitrary digital content.  A "bag" has just enough structure to enclose descriptive metadata "tags" and a file "payload" but does not require knowledge of the payload's internal semantics.  This BagIt format is suitable for reliable storage and transfer.</t></abstract>

